<br>
It seems like, at least in terms of RvR combat, the assassin classes function like submarines.  Our strength is our ability to remain undetected, launching attacks when the odds are in our favor.  We don't have the pure offensive power of other classes (carriers, battleships), but we can get to places they can't.  We're great at destroying low-levels (merchant ships) and getting away undetected.  When we're unstealthed (on the surface), we're extremely vulnerable.  Our greatest enemy is someone just like us, only sneakier.<br>
<br>
Any more to this, or is it just in the &quot;interesting observation&quot; category?  Time to read up on submarine tactics?  Does the analogy hold true for other classes as well?  Who are the carriers, battleships, destroyers?  Is it time to watch Hunt for Red October again? <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade<br>Guinevere<br><small>Explorer 93% | Killer 60% | Socializer 40% | Achiever 6%</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 12:18:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1980.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naval Combat and the Assassin</span><hr size=1> Intriguing.<br>
