pecially the German U-boat tactics, may be helpful. <br>
<br>
Today's subs can launch cruise missles that can destroy most medium sized countries if they're nuclear tipped. A submarine is the most versatile weapon in the world, it just doesn't have the staying power of the carrier. <br>
<br>
Rogues= stealth fighter (F-117)... can launch a mean punch in the right situation... if seen they are less effective and die fairly easily... There are stealth ships coming around, one from Norway comes to mind but I'm not sure the analogy holds for rogues at least in the modern era.<br>
<br>
So... WW2 era...<br>
<br>
Casters = Aircraft carriers... everyone wants to kill one and if left unmolested can change the course of the war.<br>
<br>
Tanks = Battlships obviously... die to other battleships or unmolested aircraft carriers<br>
<br>
Assassins=  submarines... leave the battleships alone and hit the aircraft carriers first, scout, kill the support craft... etc etc<br>
<br>
Archers = Cruisers... can kill from range, are fast when neccessary... but when confronted can get pounded upon. Think Graff Spee...<br>
<br>
Great topic, thanks for getting the juices flowing...<br>
<br>
Pax<br>
